F–G, 4 F–G, 7 F–G, E, 10 A, 11 A–D, 19 A–H.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,1629,2015]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis box="[151,209,1629,1655]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<collectingRegion box="[151,209,1629,1655]" country="Maldives" name="Maale" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Male</collectingRegion>
</emphasis>
. Deep piceous throughout. Crown pale yellow. Eyes silvery white, ocelli transparent. Forewing piceous with narrow flavous band along costal margin, venation light brown. Apices of hind femur, tibiae and tarsomere black, macrosetae on hind tibiae dark brown to light brown (
<figureCitation box="[754,855,1701,1727]" captionStart="FIGURES 1" captionStartId="36.[151,264,1896,1921]" captionTargetBox="[177,1410,169,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@36.[159,1428,166,1875]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURES 1 A–O. Habitus of Coelidiini species. A. Calodia deergha sp. nov., male; B. C. keralica sp. nov., male; C &amp; D. C. kodikanelensis Nielson, male and female; E. C. kumari sp. nov., male; F &amp; G. C. neofusca sp. nov., male and female; H &amp; I. C. ostenta (Distant), male and female; J. C. periyari sp. nov., male; K. C. subcrista Nielson, male; L. C. tridenta sp. nov., male; M. Glaberana acuta sp. nov., male; N &amp; O. G. khasiensis (Rao), male and female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3366546/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Figs. 1 F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[866,903,1701,1727]" captionStart="FIGURES 4" captionStartId="39.[151,264,1897,1922]" captionTargetBox="[188,1409,181,1867]" captionTargetId="figure@39.[164,1423,166,1884]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURES 4 A–O. Habitus of Coelidiini species, lateral view. A. Calodia deergha sp. nov., male; B. C. keralica sp. nov., male; C &amp; D. C. kodikanelensis Nielson, male and female; E. C. kumari sp. nov., male; F &amp; G. C. neofusca sp. nov., male and female; H &amp; I. C. ostenta (Distant), male and female; J. C. periyari sp. nov., male; K. C. subcrista Nielson, male; L. C. tridenta sp. nov., male; M. Glaberana acuta sp. nov., male; N &amp; O. G. khasiensis (Rao), male and female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3366552/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">4 F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[914,954,1701,1727]" captionStart="FIGURES 7" captionStartId="42.[151,264,1892,1917]" captionTargetBox="[175,1425,310,1744]" captionTargetId="figure@42.[151,1435,264,1750]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="FIGURES 7 A–P. Faces of Coelidiini species. A. Calodia deergha sp. nov., male; B. C. keralica sp. nov., male; C &amp; D. C. kodikanelensis Nielson, male and female; E. C. kumari sp. nov., male; F &amp; G. C. neofusca sp. nov., male and female; H &amp; I. C. ostenta (Distant), male and female; J. C. periyari sp. nov., male; K. C. subcrista Nielson, male; L. C. tridenta sp. nov., male; M. Glaberana acuta sp. nov., Male; N &amp; O. G. khasiensis (Rao), male and female. P. Glaberana purva sp. nov., male." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3366558/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">7 F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,1629,2015]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis box="[199,283,1737,1763]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Female</emphasis>
. Similar in coloration to male but paler (
<figureCitation box="[738,844,1737,1763]" captionStart="FIGURES 1" captionStartId="36.[151,264,1896,1921]" captionTargetBox="[177,1410,169,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@36.[159,1428,166,1875]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURES 1 A–O. Habitus of Coelidiini species. A. Calodia deergha sp. nov., male; B. C. keralica sp. nov., male; C &amp; D. C. kodikanelensis Nielson, male and female; E. C. kumari sp. nov., male; F &amp; G. C. neofusca sp. nov., male and female; H &amp; I. C. ostenta (Distant), male and female; J. C. periyari sp. nov., male; K. C. subcrista Nielson, male; L. C. tridenta sp. nov., male; M. Glaberana acuta sp. nov., male; N &amp; O. G. khasiensis (Rao), male and female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3366546/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Figs. 1 G</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[855,899,1737,1763]" captionStart="FIGURES 4" captionStartId="39.[151,264,1897,1922]" captionTargetBox="[188,1409,181,1867]" captionTargetId="figure@39.[164,1423,166,1884]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURES 4 A–O. Habitus of Coelidiini species, lateral view. A. Calodia deergha sp. nov., male; B. C. keralica sp. nov., male; C &amp; D. C. kodikanelensis Nielson, male and female; E. C. kumari sp. nov., male; F &amp; G. C. neofusca sp. nov., male and female; H &amp; I. C. ostenta (Distant), male and female; J. C. periyari sp. nov., male; K. C. subcrista Nielson, male; L. C. tridenta sp. nov., male; M. Glaberana acuta sp. nov., male; N &amp; O. G. khasiensis (Rao), male and female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3366552/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">4 G</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[910,955,1737,1763]" captionStart="FIGURES 7" captionStartId="42.[151,264,1892,1917]" captionTargetBox="[175,1425,310,1744]" captionTargetId="figure@42.[151,1435,264,1750]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="FIGURES 7 A–P. Faces of Coelidiini species. A. Calodia deergha sp. nov., male; B. C. keralica sp. nov., male; C &amp; D. C. kodikanelensis Nielson, male and female; E. C. kumari sp. nov., male; F &amp; G. C. neofusca sp. nov., male and female; H &amp; I. C. ostenta (Distant), male and female; J. C. periyari sp. nov., male; K. C. subcrista Nielson, male; L. C. tridenta sp. nov., male; M. Glaberana acuta sp. nov., Male; N &amp; O. G. khasiensis (Rao), male and female. P. Glaberana purva sp. nov., male." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3366558/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">7 G</figureCitation>
). Seventh sternite slightly convex medially (
<figureCitation box="[160,269,1773,1799]" captionStart="FIGURES 10" captionStartId="45.[151,264,1908,1933]" captionTargetBox="[228,1374,181,1870]" captionTargetId="figure@45.[197,1391,166,1888]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="FIGURES 10 A–L. Female sternite VII of Coelidiini. A. Calodia neofusca sp. nov.; B. C. ostenta (Distant); C. C. kodikanelensis Nielson; D. Glaberana khasiensis (Rao). E. Olidiana brevis (Walker); F. O. kirkaldyi (Nielson); G. O. umroensis sp. nov.; H. Singillatus serratispatulatus sp. nov.; I. Trinoridia dialata sp. nov.; J. T. piperica sp. nov.; K. T. ramamurthyi sp. nov.; L. Webbolidia andamana sp. nov.; L." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3366564/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Fig. 10 A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,1629,2015]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis box="[199,370,1809,1835]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<collectingRegion box="[199,257,1809,1835]" country="Maldives" name="Maale" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Male</collectingRegion>
genitalia.
</emphasis>
Pygofer without caudoventral process, small lobe on caudodorsal margin (
<figureCitation box="[1205,1316,1809,1835]" captionStart="FIGURES 19" captionStartId="54.[151,264,1962,1987]" captionTargetBox="[175,1384,197,1943]" captionTargetId="figure@54.[165,1423,166,1943]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="FIGURES 19 A–H. Calodia neofusca sp. nov., male genitalia. A &amp; B. Aedeagus, dorsal view; C &amp; D. Aedeagus, lateral view; E. Subgenital plate, dorsal view; F. Style, dorsal view; G. Connective, dorsal view; H. Pygofer, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3366582/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Fig. 19 H</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate long, broad medially, with small hair-like setae on outer lateral margin (
<figureCitation box="[1046,1153,1845,1871]" captionStart="FIGURES 19" captionStartId="54.[151,264,1962,1987]" captionTargetBox="[175,1384,197,1943]" captionTargetId="figure@54.[165,1423,166,1943]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="FIGURES 19 A–H. Calodia neofusca sp. nov., male genitalia. A &amp; B. Aedeagus, dorsal view; C &amp; D. Aedeagus, lateral view; E. Subgenital plate, dorsal view; F. Style, dorsal view; G. Connective, dorsal view; H. Pygofer, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3366582/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Fig. 19 E</figureCitation>
). Style short and broad at base, blunt at apex (
<figureCitation box="[373,479,1881,1907]" captionStart="FIGURES 19" captionStartId="54.[151,264,1962,1987]" captionTargetBox="[175,1384,197,1943]" captionTargetId="figure@54.[165,1423,166,1943]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="FIGURES 19 A–H. Calodia neofusca sp. nov., male genitalia. A &amp; B. Aedeagus, dorsal view; C &amp; D. Aedeagus, lateral view; E. Subgenital plate, dorsal view; F. Style, dorsal view; G. Connective, dorsal view; H. Pygofer, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3366582/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Fig. 19 F</figureCitation>
). Connective as long as wide at base (
<figureCitation box="[901,1011,1881,1907]" captionStart="FIGURES 19" captionStartId="54.[151,264,1962,1987]" captionTargetBox="[175,1384,197,1943]" captionTargetId="figure@54.[165,1423,166,1943]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="FIGURES 19 A–H. Calodia neofusca sp. nov., male genitalia. A &amp; B. Aedeagus, dorsal view; C &amp; D. Aedeagus, lateral view; E. Subgenital plate, dorsal view; F. Style, dorsal view; G. Connective, dorsal view; H. Pygofer, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3366582/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Fig. 19 G</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus slightly curved dorsally at apex in lateral view, with two subapical spine-like processes, distal process arising from lateral margin and directed basad and without secondary spines, proximal one with numerous long secondary spines throughout; gonopore small, subapical, arising distad of proximal process (
<figureCitation box="[740,832,1989,2015]" captionStart="FIGURES 19" captionStartId="54.[151,264,1962,1987]" captionTargetBox="[175,1384,197,1943]" captionTargetId="figure@54.[165,1423,166,1943]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="FIGURES 19 A–H. Calodia neofusca sp. nov., male genitalia. A &amp; B. Aedeagus, dorsal view; C &amp; D. Aedeagus, lateral view; E. Subgenital plate, dorsal view; F. Style, dorsal view; G. Connective, dorsal view; H. Pygofer, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3366582/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Figs. 19</figureCitation>
A–D).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,153,647]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis box="[199,397,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Female genitalia.</emphasis>
Valvula I, in lateral view, with apex acute; dorsal sculptured area confined to distal 1/3 (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 11" captionStartId="46.[151,264,1929,1954]" captionTargetBox="[187,1369,186,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@46.[151,1436,181,1894]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURES 11 A–P. Female valvulae I and II. Calodia neofusca sp. nov.: A &amp; B. Valvula I; C &amp; D. Valvula II. C. ostenta (Distant): E&amp; F. Valvula I; G &amp; H. Valvula II. C. kodikanelensis Nielson: I &amp; J. Valvula I; K &amp; L. Valvula II. Glaberana khasiensis (Rao): M &amp; N. Valvula I; O &amp; P. Valvula II." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3366566/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Figs. 11</figureCitation>
A–B). Valvula II, somewhat sinuate in lateral view, toothed area occupying apical 1/3 (11 C–D).
</paragraph>
